ures]] / [[Paramount Players]]  || [[Michael Matthews (director)|Michael Matthews]] (director); [[Matthew Robinson (writer)|Matthew Robinson]] (screenplay); [[Dylan O'Brien]], [[Michael Rooker]], [[Ariana Greenblatt]], [[Jessica Henwick]] ||<center><ref>[https://deadline.com/2020/02/blue-story-gang-saga-film-release-date-moved-by-paramount-1202860719/ Controversial Gang Saga \u2018Blue Story\u2019 Release Date Moved By Paramount]</ref></center>\n|-\n| ''Dog'' || [[Metro-Goldwyn-Mayer]] || [[Channing Tatum]] (director), [[Reid Carolin]] (director/screenplay); Channing Tatum ||<center><ref>[https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/mgm-picks-up-channing-tatums-road-comedy-dog-1282195 MGM Picks Up Channing Tatum's Road Comedy 'Dog']</ref></center>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\"| 26\n| ''[[Nobody (film)|Nobody]]'' || [[Universal Pictures]] || [[Ilya Naishuller]] (director); [[Derek Kolstad]] (screenplay); [[Bob Odenkirk]], [[Connie Nielsen]], [[Christopher Lloyd]] ||<center><ref>[https://deadline.com/2020/04/m-night-shyamalan-bob-odenkirk-nobody-universal-movie-release-date-change-1202902785/ Universal Moves Bob Odenkirk Action Thriller \u2018Nobody\u2019 Out Of August; M. Night Shyamalan Thriller Undated For Now]</ref></center>\n|-\n| ''Ron's Gone Wrong'' || [[20th Century Studios]] / [[20th Century Fox Animation]] || Alessandro Carloni, Jean-Philippe Vine (director); Peter Baynham, Sarah Smith (screenplay) ||<center><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://variety.com/2019/film/news/ridley-scott-the-last-duel-disney-dates-christmas-2020-1203406933/|title=Ridley Scott's 'The Last Duel' Gets the Greenlight as Disney Dates Multiple Titles|last=Kroll|first=Justin|last2=Kroll|first2=Justin|date=2019-11-16|website=Variety|language=en|access-date=2019-11-16}}</ref></center>\n|-\n! rowspan=\"11\" style=\"text-align:center; background:#87f7bf; textcolor:#000;\" |M<br>A<br>R<br>C<br>H\n| rowspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\" | 5\n| ''[[Ghostbusters: Afterlife]]'' || [[Col