cho Kielland]], Norwegian jurist and journalist (b. [[1854]])\n* [[May 6]]\n** [[Franz von Lenbach]], German pahinter (b. [[1836]])\n** [[Alexander William Williamson]], English chemist (b. [[1824]])\n* [[May 7]] \n** [[Manuel Candamo]], Peruvian politician, 23rd [[President of Peru]] (b. [[1841]])\n** [[\u00c9mile-Jules Dubois]], French doctor (b. [[1853]])\n* [[May 8]] \n** [[Richard Xavier Baxter]], Canadian [[Roman Catholic]] priest and venerable (b. [[1821]])\n** [[Eadweard Muybridge]], British photographer and motion picture pioneer (b. [[1830]])\n* [[May 9]]\n** [[George Johnston Allman]], Irish mathematician, scholar and historian (b. [[1824]])\n** [[Aleksandar Bresztyenszky]], Croatian writer (b. [[1843]])\n** [[Bonaventura Gargiulo]], Italian [[Order of Friars Minor Capuchin|Capuchin]] monk and [[Roman Catholic]] bishop (b. [[1843]])\n* [[May 10]]\n** [[\u00c9mile Sarrau]], French chemist (b. [[1837]])\n** [[Henry Morton Stanley|Sir Henry Morton Stanley]], British explorer (b. [[1841]])\n* [[May 11]]\n** [[Hans Grisebach]], German architect (b. [[1846]])\n** [[Eugen Kumi\u010di\u0107]], Croatian writer (b. [[1850]])\n* [[May 12]] &ndash; [[Isabella Eug\u00e9nie Boyer]], French model (b. [[1841]])\n* [[May 13]]\n** [[Walter Carpenter]], British admiral (b. [[1834]])\n** [[Ottokar Lorenz]], German genealogist (b. [[1832]])\n* [[May 14]] \n** [[Rita Barcelo y Pages]], Spanish [[Augustinian]] religious sister and servant of God (b. [[1843]])\n** [[Fyodor Bredikhin]], Russian astronomer (b. [[1831]])\n* [[May 15]] &ndash; [[\u00c9tienne-Jules Marey]], French inventor (b. [[1830]])\n* [[May 16]] &ndash; [[Harold Finch-Hatton]], British politician (b. [[1856]])\n* [[May 17]] \n** [[Tom\u00e1s C\u00e1mara y Castro]], Spanish [[Roman Catholic]] bishop (b. [[1847]])\n** [[Fran\u00e7ois Coillard]], French missionary (b. [[1834]])\n** [[Princess Pauline of Saxe-Weimar-Eisenach]] (b. [[1852]])\n* [[May 19]] &ndash;\n** [[Auguste Molinier]], French historian (b. [[1851]])\n** [[Jamsetji Tata]], Indian industrialist (b. [[1839]])\n* [[May 21]] &ndash; [[Duke Paul Frederick of Mecklenburg (1882\u20131904)|Duke Paul Frederick of Mecklenburg]] (b. [[1882]])\n* [[May 22]] &ndash; [[Charles Elwood Brown]], [[U.S. Representative]] from [[Ohio]] (b. [[1834]])\n* [[May 24]] &ndash; [[Duchess Maria Isabella of W\u00fcrttemberg]] (b. [[1871]])\n* [[May 26]] &ndash; [[Mary Ellen Bagnall-Oakeley]], English antiquarian, author, and painter (b. [[1833]])\n* [[May 27]] &ndash; [[An\u0111elko Aleksi\u0107]], Serbian general (b. [[1876]])\n* [[May 29]] &ndash; [[Manuel Mar\u00eda de Zamacona y Murphy]], Mexican politician (b. [[1829]])\n* [[May 30]]\n** [[Frederick William, Grand Duke of Mecklenburg-Strelitz]] (b. [[1819]])\n** [[Marta Anna Wiecka]], Polish [[Roman Catholic]] religious professed and blessed (b. [[1874]])\n\n=== June ===\n* [[June 1]] &ndash; [[Ivan Kondratyev]], Russian writer (b. [[1849]])\n* [[June 3]] &ndash; [[Vincent Tancred]], South African cricketer (b. [[1875]])\n* [[June 4]]\n** [[Muhammad bin Yahya Hamid ad-Din]], [[Imam of Yemen]] (b. [[1839]])\n** [[George Frederick Phillips]], Canadian-born military hero (b. [[1862]])\n** [[Princess Marie of Hanover]] (b. [[1849]])\n* [[June 9]] &ndash; [[Kwasi Boakye]], Dutch engineer (b. [[1827]])\n* [[June 12]] &ndash; [[Camille of Renesse-Breidbach]], Belgian Count (b. [[1836]])\n* [[June 14]] &ndash; [[Richard Knill Freeman]], British architect (b. [[1840]])\n* [[June 16]] \n** [[Nikolay Bobrikov]], Russian soldier, politician and Governor-General of Finland (b. [[1839]])\n** [[Manuel Uribe \u00c1ngel]], Colombian physician (b. [[1822]])\n* [[June 18]]\n** [[Sami Frash\u00ebri]], Albanian writer (b. [[1850]])\n** [[Celia Logan]], American actress (b. [[1837]])\n* [[June 22]] &ndash; [[Karl Ritter von Stremayr]], former Prime Minister of Austria (b. [[1832]])\n* [[June 27]] &ndash; [[Anatole Jean-Baptiste Antoine de Barth\u00e9lemy]], French archaeologist (b. [[1821]])\n* [[June 28]] &ndash; [[Aurora Pavlovna Demidova|Princess and Countess Aurora Pavlovna Demidova]] (b. [[1873]])\n* [[June 29]] &ndash; [[Tom Emmett]], English cricketer (b. [[1841]])\n* [[June 30]] &ndash; [[Pablo de Anda Padilla]], Mexican [[Roman Catholic]] priest and venerable (b. [[1830]])\n\n=== July ===\n[[File:Theodor Herzl.jpg|thumb|110px|[[Theodor Herzl]]]]\n[[File:Joseph-Paul Blanc photo.jpg|thumb|110px|[[Joseph Blanc]]]]\n[[File:Edouard Thilges.jpg|thumb|110px|[[\u00c9douard Thilges]]]]\n[[File:KrugerPaulusJohannes.jpg|thumb|110px|[[Paul Kruger]]]]\n* [[July 1]] &ndash; [[George Frederic Watts]], British [[Symbolism (arts)|symbolist]] painter and sculptor (b. [[1817]])\n* [[July 2]] &ndash; [[Eug\u00e9nie Joubert]], French [[Roman Catholic]] religious professed and blessed (b. [[1876]])\n* [[July 3]] \n** [[John Bell Hatcher]], American paleontologist (b. [[1861]])\n** [[Theodor Herzl]], Austrian founder of Zionism (b. [[1860]])\n* [[July 4]] &ndash; [[B\u00f3dog Czorda]], Hungarian politician (b. [[1828]])\n* [[July 5]] \n** [[Joseph Blanc]], French painter (b. [[1846]])\n** [[Joseph Evans (politician)|Joseph Evans]], British-born Australian politician (b. [[1837]])\n** [[Matsudaira Yasuhide]], Japanese daimy\u014d (b. [[1830]])\n* [[July 6]] &ndash; [[Abai Qunanbaiuly]], Kazakh poet (b. [[1845]])\n* [[July 7]] &ndash; [[Adolph Friedl\u00e4nder]], German lithographer (b. [[1851]])\n* [[July 9]] &ndash; [[\u00c9douard Thilges]], Luxembourgish politician, 7th [[Prime Minister of Luxembourg]] (b. [[1817]])\n* [[July 14]] &ndash; [[Paul Kruger]], South African military and political figure, 3rd [[President of South Africa]] (b. [[1825]])\n* [[July 15]] &ndash; [[Anton Chekhov]], Russian writer (b. [[1860]])\n* [[July 17]] &ndash; [[Isaac Roberts]], Welsh astronomer (b. [[1829]])\n* [[July 19]] &ndash; [[Herbert Campbell]], English actor (b. [[1844]])\n* [[July 22]] &ndash; [[Wilson Barrett]], English actor and playwright (b. [[1846]])\n* [[July 23]]\n** [[Isa\u00edas Gamboa]], Colombian poet (b. [[1872]])\n** [[Rodolfo Amando Philippi]], German\u2013born Chilean paleontologist and zoologist (b. [[1808]])\n* [[July 26]] &ndash; [[Henry Clay Taylor]], American admiral (b. [[1845]])\n* [[July 30]] &ndash; [[Richard A. Harrison]], [[U.S. House of Representatives]] from [[Ohio]] (b. [[1824]])\n\n=== August ===\n[[File:Pierre Waldeck-Rousseau by Nadar.jpg|thumb|110px|[[Pierre Waldeck-Rousseau]]]]\n[[File:Gaudensi Allar.jpg|thumb|110px|[[Gaudensi Allar]]]]\n[[File:Portrait of Murad V.jpg|thumb|110px|Sultan [[Murad V]]]]\n* [[August 3]] &ndash; [[Ernst Jedliczka]], Russian-born German pianist (b. [[1855]])\n* [[August 6]] &ndash; [[Eduard Hanslick]], Austrian music critic (b. [[1825]])\n* [[August 8]] &ndash; [[John Innes (philanthropist)|John Innes]], British philanthropist (b. [[1828]])\n* [[August 9]] \n** [[Joseph David Everett]], English physicist (b. [[1831]])\n** [[Friedrich Ratzel]], German geographer and ethnographer (b. [[1844]])\n* [[August 10]]\n** [[Wilgelm Vitgeft]], Russian admiral (killed in action) (b. [[1847]])\n** [[Pierre Waldeck-Rousseau]], French politician, 29th [[Prime Minister of France]] (b. [[1846]])\n* [[August 12]]\n** [[Kawamura Sumiyoshi]], Japanese admiral (b. [[1836]])\n** [[William Renshaw]], British tennis player (b. [[1861]])\n* [[August 13]] &ndash; [[Elizabeth Wellesley, Duchess of Wellington]] (b. [[1820]])\n* [[August 14]] &ndash; [[Eduard von Martens]], German zoologist (b. [[1831]])\n* [[August 15]] &ndash; [[John Henry Kinkead]], American businessman and politician, 1st [[Governor of Alaska]] and 3rd [[Governor of Nevada]] (b. [[1826]])\n* [[August 16]] \n** [[Joachim Grassi]], Italian architect (b. [[1837]])\n** [[Prentiss Ingraham]], American author of dime fiction (b. [[1843]])\n* [[August 22]]\n** [[Gaudensi Allar]], French architect (b. [[1841]])\n** [[Kate Chopin]], American author (b. [[1850]])\n* [[August 25]] &ndash; [[Henri Fantin-Latour]], French painter (b. [[1836]])\n* [[August 29]]